      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, formal use-error analysis is not required; analyst qualification and peer review of simulation setup are sufficient.",
      "rationale": "Simulations performed by PhD-level CFD analyst with 8 years cardiovascular CFD experience. Setup reviewed by independent senior analyst. Formal use-error FMEA not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, model form uncertainty need not be formally quantified; selection of governing equations and constitutive models documented with literature justification.",
      "rationale": "RANS k-omega SST turbulence model selected based on published cardiovascular pump CFD literature. Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model adopted per FDA guidance. Model form uncertainty not formally quantified; acceptable at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, sensitivity analysis on model inputs is not required; nominal input values documented with sources.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs (fluid density, viscosity coefficients, hemolysis model constants) documented with literature sources and measurement references. Formal sensitivity analysis not required at MRL 2."
